  "suggestion": "Smaller, greedier organisms outsurvived larger ones. Efficiency scales inversely with particle count and baseRadius. Prune form complexity, sharpen resource sensors.; Efficiency is the critical bottleneck at 0.388 (dragging down overall fitness). Two organisms died early (IDs 0, 3 — both 13 particles, short lifespans), while 8-particle survivors thrived to age 500. Root cause: oversized forms burning energy faster than resources sustain them. Fix: (1) Reduce particle budgets + baseRadius to lower energy drain, (2) Increase resourceAttraction and harvestThreshold to ensure survivors capture enough energy, (3) Increase energyConserve to stretch resources further. Survival rate will improve as a second-order effect. Beauty is acceptable at 0.67 — prioritize efficiency gains.",
